			<p>Hello Maeve,</p>
<p>The reason author is being criticized for that is because the plugin is a premium plugin that doesn&#8217;t easily auto update without extra work for it. So many site owners might go through the tedious updating process based on the news feed that the author is giving them when a new release is made. If they see some small bug fixes or feature changes that don&#8217;t really affect them on everyday basis then they might prolong the update.</p>
