			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/22da4a2d964f1ff5ab242cce0f21809d?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/22da4a2d964f1ff5ab242cce0f21809d?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name">dan</span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-09-29T05:11:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2014/09/slider-revolution-plugin-critical-vulnerability-being-exploited.html#comment-4067">September 29, 2014</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>if you can&#8217;t update the slider you can block access to the config file in your .htaccess file </p>
<p>RewriteCond %{QUERY_STRING} wp-config.php [NC]<br />
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ index.php [F,L] </p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
